This paper deals with the task of automatically colorizing digital art, which falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks for this task, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves the processing of visual data, which is relevant to computer graphics (cs.GR). The use of adversarial networks is also mentioned, which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with the application of the proposed method to digital art, which is a subfield of multimedia (cs.MM).
